def string_with_arrows(text, pos_start, pos_end): 
 9def string_with_arrows(text, pos_start, pos_end):
10	result = ''
11
12	# Calculate indices
13	idx_start = max(text.rfind('\n', 0, pos_start.idx), 0)
14	idx_end = text.find('\n', idx_start + 1)
15	if idx_end < 0: idx_end = len(text)
16	
17	# Generate each line
18	line_count = pos_end.ln - pos_start.ln + 1
19	for i in range(line_count):
20		# Calculate line columns
21		line = text[idx_start:idx_end]
22		col_start = pos_start.col if i == 0 else 0
23		col_end = pos_end.col if i == line_count - 1 else len(line) - 1
24
25		# Append to result
26		result += line + '\n'
27		result += ' ' * col_start + '^' * (col_end - col_start)
28
29		# Re-calculate indices
30		idx_start = idx_end
31		idx_end = text.find('\n', idx_start + 1)
32		if idx_end < 0: idx_end = len(text)
33
34	return result.replace('\t', '')

 81class RTError(Error):
 82  def __init__(self, pos_start, pos_end, details, context):
 83    super().__init__(pos_start, pos_end, 'Runtime Error', details)
 84    self.context = context

 86  def as_string(self):
 87    result  = self.generate_traceback()
 88    result += f'{self.error_name}: {self.details}'
 89    result += '\n\n' + string_with_arrows(self.pos_start.ftxt, self.pos_start, self.pos_end)
 90    return result
 91
 92  def generate_traceback(self):
 93    result = ''
 94    pos = self.pos_start
 95    ctx = self.context
 96
 97    while ctx:
 98      result = f'  File {pos.fn}, line {str(pos.ln + 1)}, in {ctx.display_name}\n' + result
 99      pos = ctx.parent_entry_pos
100      ctx = ctx.parent
101
102    return 'Traceback (most recent call last):\n' + result

class Lexer: 
203class Lexer:
204  def __init__(self, fn, text):
205    self.fn = fn
206    self.text = text
207    self.pos = Position(-1, 0, -1, fn, text)
208    self.current_char = None
209    self.advance()
210  
211  def advance(self):
212    self.pos.advance(self.current_char)
213    self.current_char = self.text[self.pos.idx] if self.pos.idx < len(self.text) else None
214
215  def make_tokens(self):
216    tokens = []
217
218    while self.current_char != None:
219      if self.current_char in ' \t':
220        self.advance()
221      elif self.current_char == '#':
222        self.skip_comment()
223      elif self.current_char in ';\n':
224        tokens.append(Token(TT_NEWLINE, pos_start=self.pos))
225        self.advance()
226      elif self.current_char in DIGITS:
227        tokens.append(self.make_number())
228      elif self.current_char in LETTERS:
229        tokens.append(self.make_identifier())
230      elif self.current_char == '"':
231        tokens.append(self.make_string())
232      elif self.current_char == '+':
233        tokens.append(Token(TT_PLUS, pos_start=self.pos))
234        self.advance()
235      elif self.current_char == '-':
236        tokens.append(self.make_minus_or_arrow())
237      elif self.current_char == '*':
238        tokens.append(Token(TT_MUL, pos_start=self.pos))
239        self.advance()
240      elif self.current_char == '/':
241        tokens.append(Token(TT_DIV, pos_start=self.pos))
242        self.advance()
243      elif self.current_char == '^':
244        tokens.append(Token(TT_POW, pos_start=self.pos))
245        self.advance()
246      elif self.current_char == '(':
247        tokens.append(Token(TT_LPAREN, pos_start=self.pos))
248        self.advance()
249      elif self.current_char == ')':
250        tokens.append(Token(TT_RPAREN, pos_start=self.pos))
251        self.advance()
252      elif self.current_char == '[':
253        tokens.append(Token(TT_LSQUARE, pos_start=self.pos))
254        self.advance()
255      elif self.current_char == ']':
256        tokens.append(Token(TT_RSQUARE, pos_start=self.pos))
257        self.advance()
258      elif self.current_char == '!':
259        token, error = self.make_not_equals()
260        if error: return [], error
261        tokens.append(token)
262      elif self.current_char == '=':
263        tokens.append(self.make_equals())
264      elif self.current_char == '<':
265        tokens.append(self.make_less_than())
266      elif self.current_char == '>':
267        tokens.append(self.make_greater_than())
268      elif self.current_char == ',':
269        tokens.append(Token(TT_COMMA, pos_start=self.pos))
270        self.advance()
271      else:
272        pos_start = self.pos.copy()
273        char = self.current_char
274        self.advance()
275        return [], IllegalCharError(pos_start, self.pos, "'" + char + "'")
276
277    tokens.append(Token(TT_EOF, pos_start=self.pos))
278    return tokens, None
279
280  def make_number(self):
281    num_str = ''
282    dot_count = 0
283    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
284
285    while self.current_char != None and self.current_char in DIGITS + '.':
286      if self.current_char == '.':
287        if dot_count == 1: break
288        dot_count += 1
289      num_str += self.current_char
290      self.advance()
291
292    if dot_count == 0:
293      return Token(TT_INT, int(num_str), pos_start, self.pos)
294    else:
295      return Token(TT_FLOAT, float(num_str), pos_start, self.pos)
296
297  def make_string(self):
298    string = ''
299    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
300    escape_character = False
301    self.advance()
302
303    escape_characters = {
304      'n': '\n',
305      't': '\t'
306    }
307
308    while self.current_char != None and (self.current_char != '"' or escape_character):
309      if escape_character:
310        string += escape_characters.get(self.current_char, self.current_char)
311      else:
312        if self.current_char == '\\':
313          escape_character = True
314        else:
315          string += self.current_char
316      self.advance()
317      escape_character = False
318    
319    self.advance()
320    return Token(TT_STRING, string, pos_start, self.pos)
321
322  def make_identifier(self):
323    id_str = ''
324    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
325
326    while self.current_char != None and self.current_char in LETTERS_DIGITS + '_':
327      id_str += self.current_char
328      self.advance()
329
330    tok_type = TT_KEYWORD if id_str in KEYWORDS else TT_IDENTIFIER
331    return Token(tok_type, id_str, pos_start, self.pos)
332
333  def make_minus_or_arrow(self):
334    tok_type = TT_MINUS
335    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
336    self.advance()
337
338    if self.current_char == '>':
339      self.advance()
340      tok_type = TT_ARROW
341
342    return Token(tok_type, pos_start=pos_start, pos_end=self.pos)
343
344  def make_not_equals(self):
345    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
346    self.advance()
347
348    if self.current_char == '=':
349      self.advance()
350      return Token(TT_NE, pos_start=pos_start, pos_end=self.pos), None
351
352    self.advance()
353    return None, ExpectedCharError(pos_start, self.pos, "'=' (after '!')")
354  
355  def make_equals(self):
356    tok_type = TT_EQ
357    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
358    self.advance()
359
360    if self.current_char == '=':
361      self.advance()
362      tok_type = TT_EE
363
364    return Token(tok_type, pos_start=pos_start, pos_end=self.pos)
365
366  def make_less_than(self):
367    tok_type = TT_LT
368    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
369    self.advance()
370
371    if self.current_char == '=':
372      self.advance()
373      tok_type = TT_LTE
374
375    return Token(tok_type, pos_start=pos_start, pos_end=self.pos)
376
377  def make_greater_than(self):
378    tok_type = TT_GT
379    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
380    self.advance()
381
382    if self.current_char == '=':
383      self.advance()
384      tok_type = TT_GTE
385
386    return Token(tok_type, pos_start=pos_start, pos_end=self.pos)
387
388  def skip_comment(self):
389    self.advance()
390
391    while self.current_char and self.current_char != '\n':
392      self.advance()
393
394    self.advance()

220        self.advance()
221      elif self.current_char == '#':
222        self.skip_comment()
223      elif self.current_char in ';\n':
224        tokens.append(Token(TT_NEWLINE, pos_start=self.pos))
225        self.advance()
226      elif self.current_char in DIGITS:
227        tokens.append(self.make_number())
228      elif self.current_char in LETTERS:
229        tokens.append(self.make_identifier())
230      elif self.current_char == '"':
231        tokens.append(self.make_string())
232      elif self.current_char == '+':
233        tokens.append(Token(TT_PLUS, pos_start=self.pos))
234        self.advance()
235      elif self.current_char == '-':
236        tokens.append(self.make_minus_or_arrow())
237      elif self.current_char == '*':
238        tokens.append(Token(TT_MUL, pos_start=self.pos))
239        self.advance()
240      elif self.current_char == '/':
241        tokens.append(Token(TT_DIV, pos_start=self.pos))
242        self.advance()
243      elif self.current_char == '^':
244        tokens.append(Token(TT_POW, pos_start=self.pos))
245        self.advance()
246      elif self.current_char == '(':
247        tokens.append(Token(TT_LPAREN, pos_start=self.pos))
248        self.advance()
249      elif self.current_char == ')':
250        tokens.append(Token(TT_RPAREN, pos_start=self.pos))
251        self.advance()
252      elif self.current_char == '[':
253        tokens.append(Token(TT_LSQUARE, pos_start=self.pos))
254        self.advance()
255      elif self.current_char == ']':
256        tokens.append(Token(TT_RSQUARE, pos_start=self.pos))
257        self.advance()
258      elif self.current_char == '!':
259        token, error = self.make_not_equals()
260        if error: return [], error
261        tokens.append(token)
262      elif self.current_char == '=':
263        tokens.append(self.make_equals())
264      elif self.current_char == '<':
265        tokens.append(self.make_less_than())
266      elif self.current_char == '>':
267        tokens.append(self.make_greater_than())
268      elif self.current_char == ',':
269        tokens.append(Token(TT_COMMA, pos_start=self.pos))
270        self.advance()
271      else:
272        pos_start = self.pos.copy()
273        char = self.current_char
274        self.advance()
275        return [], IllegalCharError(pos_start, self.pos, "'" + char + "'")
276
277    tokens.append(Token(TT_EOF, pos_start=self.pos))
278    return tokens, None
def make_number(self): 
280  def make_number(self):
281    num_str = ''
282    dot_count = 0
283    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
284
285    while self.current_char != None and self.current_char in DIGITS + '.':
286      if self.current_char == '.':
287        if dot_count == 1: break
288        dot_count += 1
289      num_str += self.current_char
290      self.advance()
291
292    if dot_count == 0:
293      return Token(TT_INT, int(num_str), pos_start, self.pos)
294    else:
295      return Token(TT_FLOAT, float(num_str), pos_start, self.pos)
def make_string(self): 
297  def make_string(self):
298    string = ''
299    pos_start = self.pos.copy()
300    escape_character = False
301    self.advance()
302
303    escape_characters = {
304      'n': '\n',
305      't': '\t'
306    }
307
308    while self.current_char != None and (self.current_char != '"' or escape_character):
309      if escape_character:
310        string += escape_characters.get(self.current_char, self.current_char)
311      else:
312        if self.current_char == '\\':
313          escape_character = True
314        else:
315          string += self.current_char
316      self.advance()
317      escape_character = False
318    
319    self.advance()
320    return Token(TT_STRING, string, pos_start, self.pos)

class Parser: 
 580class Parser:
 581  def __init__(self, tokens):
 582    self.tokens = tokens
 583    self.tok_idx = -1
 584    self.advance()
 585
 586  def advance(self):
 587    self.tok_idx += 1
 588    self.update_current_tok()
 589    return self.current_tok
 590
 591  def reverse(self, amount=1):
 592    self.tok_idx -= amount
 593    self.update_current_tok()
 594    return self.current_tok
 595
 596  def update_current_tok(self):
 597    if self.tok_idx >= 0 and self.tok_idx < len(self.tokens):
 598      self.current_tok = self.tokens[self.tok_idx]
 599
 600  def parse(self):
 601    res = self.statements()
 602    if not res.error and self.current_tok.type != TT_EOF:
 603      return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 604        self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,
 605        "Token cannot appear after previous tokens"
 606      ))
 607    return res
 608
 609  ###################################
 610
 611  def statements(self):
 612    res = ParseResult()
 613    statements = []
 614    pos_start = self.current_tok.pos_start.copy()
 615
 616    while self.current_tok.type == TT_NEWLINE:
 617      res.register_advancement()
 618      self.advance()
 619
 620    statement = res.register(self.statement())
 621    if res.error: return res
 622    statements.append(statement)
 623
 624    more_statements = True
 625
 626    while True:
 627      newline_count = 0
 628      while self.current_tok.type == TT_NEWLINE:
 629        res.register_advancement()
 630        self.advance()
 631        newline_count += 1
 632      if newline_count == 0:
 633        more_statements = False
 634      
 635      if not more_statements: break
 636      statement = res.try_register(self.statement())
 637      if not statement:
 638        self.reverse(res.to_reverse_count)
 639        more_statements = False
 640        continue
 641      statements.append(statement)
 642
 643    return res.success(ListNode(
 644      statements,
 645      pos_start,
 646      self.current_tok.pos_end.copy()
 647    ))
 648
 649  def statement(self):
 650    res = ParseResult()
 651    pos_start = self.current_tok.pos_start.copy()
 652
 653    if self.current_tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'return'):
 654      res.register_advancement()
 655      self.advance()
 656
 657      expr = res.try_register(self.expr())
 658      if not expr:
 659        self.reverse(res.to_reverse_count)
 660      return res.success(ReturnNode(expr, pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_start.copy()))
 661    
 662    if self.current_tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'continue'):
 663      res.register_advancement()
 664      self.advance()
 665      return res.success(ContinueNode(pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_start.copy()))
 666      
 667    if self.current_tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'break'):
 668      res.register_advancement()
 669      self.advance()
 670      return res.success(BreakNode(pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_start.copy()))
 671
 672    expr = res.register(self.expr())
 673    if res.error:
 674      return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 675        self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,
 676        "Expected 'return', 'continue', 'break', 'var', 'if', 'for', 'while', 'function', int, float, identifier, '+', '-', '(', '[' or 'not'"
 677      ))
 678    return res.success(expr)
 679
 680  def expr(self):
 681    res = ParseResult()
 682
 683    if self.current_tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'var'):
 684      res.register_advancement()
 685      self.advance()
 686
 687      if self.current_tok.type != TT_IDENTIFIER:
 688        return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 689          self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,
 690          "Expected identifier"
 691        ))
 692
 693      var_name = self.current_tok
 694      res.register_advancement()
 695      self.advance()
 696
 697      if self.current_tok.type != TT_EQ:
 698        return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 699          self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,
 700          "Expected '='"
 701        ))
 702
 703      res.register_advancement()
 704      self.advance()
 705      expr = res.register(self.expr())
 706      if res.error: return res
 707      return res.success(VarAssignNode(var_name, expr))
 708
 709    node = res.register(self.bin_op(self.comp_expr, ((TT_KEYWORD, 'and'), (TT_KEYWORD, 'or'))))
 710
 711    if res.error:
 712      return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 713        self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,
 714        "Expected 'var', 'if', 'for', 'while', 'function', int, float, identifier, '+', '-', '(', '[' or 'not'"
 715      ))
 716
 717    return res.success(node)

 719  def comp_expr(self):
 720    res = ParseResult()

 734      return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 735        self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,
 736        "Expected int, float, identifier, '+', '-', '(', '[', 'if', 'for', 'while', 'function' or 'not'"
 737      ))

 739    return res.success(node)

 763  def call(self):
 764    res = ParseResult()
 765    atom = res.register(self.atom())
 766    if res.error: return res
 767
 768    if self.current_tok.type == TT_LPAREN:
 769      res.register_advancement()
 770      self.advance()
 771      arg_nodes = []
 772
 773      if self.current_tok.type == TT_RPAREN:
 774        res.register_advancement()
 775        self.advance()
 776      else:
 777        arg_nodes.append(res.register(self.expr()))
 778        if res.error:
 779          return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 780            self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,

 782          ))
 783
 784        while self.current_tok.type == TT_COMMA:
 785          res.register_advancement()

 802  def atom(self):
 803    res = ParseResult()
 804    tok = self.current_tok
 805
 806    if tok.type in (TT_INT, TT_FLOAT):
 807      res.register_advancement()
 808      self.advance()
 809      return res.success(NumberNode(tok))
 810
 811    elif tok.type == TT_STRING:
 812      res.register_advancement()
 813      self.advance()
 814      return res.success(StringNode(tok))
 815
 816    elif tok.type == TT_IDENTIFIER:
 817      res.register_advancement()
 818      self.advance()
 819      return res.success(VarAccessNode(tok))
 820
 821    elif tok.type == TT_LPAREN:
 822      res.register_advancement()
 823      self.advance()
 824      expr = res.register(self.expr())
 825      if res.error: return res
 826      if self.current_tok.type == TT_RPAREN:
 827        res.register_advancement()
 828        self.advance()
 829        return res.success(expr)
 830      else:
 831        return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 832          self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,
 833          "Expected ')'"
 834        ))
 835
 836    elif tok.type == TT_LSQUARE:
 837      list_expr = res.register(self.list_expr())
 838      if res.error: return res
 839      return res.success(list_expr)
 840    
 841    elif tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'if'):
 842      if_expr = res.register(self.if_expr())
 843      if res.error: return res
 844      return res.success(if_expr)
 845
 846    elif tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'for'):
 847      for_expr = res.register(self.for_expr())
 848      if res.error: return res
 849      return res.success(for_expr)
 850
 851    elif tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'while'):
 852      while_expr = res.register(self.while_expr())
 853      if res.error: return res
 854      return res.success(while_expr)
 855
 856    elif tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'function'):
 857      func_def = res.register(self.func_def())
 858      if res.error: return res
 859      return res.success(func_def)
 860
 861    return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 862      tok.pos_start, tok.pos_end,
 863      "Expected int, float, identifier, '+', '-', '(', '[', if', 'for', 'while', 'function'"
 864    ))

 968  def if_expr_cases(self, case_keyword):
 969    res = ParseResult()
 970    cases = []
 971    else_case = None
 972
 973    if not self.current_tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, case_keyword):
 974      return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 975        self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,
 976        f"Expected '{case_keyword}'"
 977      ))
 978
 979    res.register_advancement()
 980    self.advance()
 981
 982    condition = res.register(self.expr())
 983    if res.error: return res
 984
 985    if not self.current_tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'then'):
 986      return res.failure(InvalidSyntaxError(
 987        self.current_tok.pos_start, self.current_tok.pos_end,
 988        f"Expected 'THEN'"
 989      ))
 990
 991    res.register_advancement()
 992    self.advance()
 993
 994    if self.current_tok.type == TT_NEWLINE:
 995      res.register_advancement()
 996      self.advance()
 997
 998      statements = res.register(self.statements())
 999      if res.error: return res
1000      cases.append((condition, statements, True))
1001
1002      if self.current_tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'end'):
1003        res.register_advancement()
1004        self.advance()
1005      else:
1006        all_cases = res.register(self.if_expr_b_or_c())
1007        if res.error: return res
1008        new_cases, else_case = all_cases
1009        cases.extend(new_cases)
1010    else:
1011      expr = res.register(self.statement())
1012      if res.error: return res
1013      cases.append((condition, expr, False))
1014
1015      all_cases = res.register(self.if_expr_b_or_c())
1016      if res.error: return res
1017      new_cases, else_case = all_cases
1018      cases.extend(new_cases)
1019
1020    return res.success((cases, else_case))

1268    if func_b == None:
1269      func_b = func_a
1270    
1271    res = ParseResult()
1272    left = res.register(func_a())

1275    while self.current_tok.type in ops or (self.current_tok.type, self.current_tok.value) in ops:

def statements(self): 
611  def statements(self):
612    res = ParseResult()
613    statements = []
614    pos_start = self.current_tok.pos_start.copy()
615
616    while self.current_tok.type == TT_NEWLINE:
617      res.register_advancement()
618      self.advance()
619
620    statement = res.register(self.statement())
621    if res.error: return res
622    statements.append(statement)
623
624    more_statements = True
625
626    while True:
627      newline_count = 0
628      while self.current_tok.type == TT_NEWLINE:
629        res.register_advancement()
630        self.advance()
631        newline_count += 1
632      if newline_count == 0:
633        more_statements = False
634      
635      if not more_statements: break
636      statement = res.try_register(self.statement())
637      if not statement:
638        self.reverse(res.to_reverse_count)
639        more_statements = False
640        continue
641      statements.append(statement)
642
643    return res.success(ListNode(
644      statements,
645      pos_start,
646      self.current_tok.pos_end.copy()
647    ))

def atom(self): 
802  def atom(self):
803    res = ParseResult()

816    elif tok.type == TT_IDENTIFIER:

846    elif tok.matches(TT_KEYWORD, 'for'):

1658    res = RTResult()
1659    res.register(self.check_args(arg_names, args))
1660    if res.should_return(): return res
1661    self.populate_args(arg_names, args, exec_ctx)

1998  def visit_BinOpNode(self, node, context):
1999    res = RTResult()
2000    left = res.register(self.visit(node.left_node, context))
2001    if res.should_return(): return res
2002    right = res.register(self.visit(node.right_node, context))
2003    if res.should_return(): return res
2004
2005    if node.op_tok.type == TT_PLUS:
2006      result, error = left.added_to(right)
2007    elif node.op_tok.type == TT_MINUS:
2008      result, error = left.subbed_by(right)
2009    elif node.op_tok.type == TT_MUL:
2010      result, error = left.multed_by(right)
2011    elif node.op_tok.type == TT_DIV:
2012      result, error = left.dived_by(right)
2013    elif node.op_tok.type == TT_POW:
2014      result, error = left.powed_by(right)
2015    elif node.op_tok.type == TT_EE:
2016      result, error = left.get_comparison_eq(right)
